<br>
Our guild had just AoE cleared Fear then downed the god Cazic Thule, our first legit kill, no help, just guild and applicants. A Sunday afternoon well spent!<br>
<br>
Two minutes after Cazic had been killed, something unexpected happend.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :omg --><img src=http://graffes.netfirms.com/smiley/omg.gif ALT=":omg"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="font-size:large;"><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>The entire Plane of Fear had repopped</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><br>
<br>
Of course no body expected this to happen, there was plenty of time left (or so we thought) and people we getting rezzes, checking points to hand out loot &amp; drinking celebration ales for our latest achievement.<br>
No one had been able to camp in time, a few maybe gated, some Fd'd, but the majority: wiped <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :x --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/sick.gif ALT=":x"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
So as we were picking up our jaws and it turns out that in the repop CT's corpse had poofed. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :cry --><img src=http://graffes.netfirms.com/smiley/cry.gif ALT=":cry"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   CT's brain had dropped and I was 99% certain I would get it (we use a dkp system for loot). Ah well, easy come, easy go. <br>
<br>
In between calls for petitions we found out that there were NO GM's around to answer petitions, being a Sunday afternoon there was little chance of getting an answer, let alone having anything done.<br>
<br>
Our patient Fd crew rolled up their sleeves and began the long task of gathering the bodies to the west camp <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :\ --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/ohwell.gif ALT=":\"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
All the while, the raid force has gathered at the Fear portal, mages making summoned armour, everyone getting ready for their least favourite raid idea: <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>The Naked Fear break</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :eek --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/eek.gif ALT=":eek"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Our guild leader starts moving people around groups, I pour myself another vodka, thinking about how long it will take to break fear if you keep throwing naked (albeit hardcore, good but still naked) players at the mobs. Naked Wizards wont last long, I think, but we're going to need all the dps we can get.<br>
At least I'm not equipment dependent, like the melee classes, I muse, I can make a hefty dent in the mobs.<br>
<br>
Seems our raid leader was thinking the same thing. I'm put into a group with our highest chanter, cleric, and three other Wizards. <br>
<br>
The penny drops <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :o --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/embarassed.gif ALT=":o"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
We're going to PbAoE Fear<br>
<br>
And we're still naked <br>
<br>
I'm not going to forget that moment of realisation for a long time. Taking Cazic, even though he is a big mofo, had gone by the book, everyone knew what to do, saftey in numbers, we owned him.<br>
This was different. Our one AoE group and a few Fd melee had to clear the area and hold it while we rezzed people back in. Everyone was depending on us, and we were playing a big risk / big reward hand.<br>
<br>
Luckily I always keep this handy:<br>
<!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.strike9.com/file.aspx/path=/Taziir/fullsize/CanOwoopAss.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
<br>
I cant remember how long we were fighting, I lost track of time. We used our skills as best we knew how, we had to. Mobs pouring towards the camp (or were they being pulled?), insane and angry that anyone would be healing THEIR enemies in THEIR plane. Our few melee rounding up strays while we Wizards throw wave after wave of destruction down onto the mobs.<br>
Slowley the rezzed came back to life, to fight, giving us wizards precious seconds to med, loot our copses and jump back into the fray.<br>
<br>
The adrelanin slowly subsided. The pile of guildies has been replaced by Fear mobs, big and small. We port everyone out, I begin to breath again. <br>
<br>
<br>
We had Downed Cazic Thule for the first time.<br>
And more importantly, avoided a 6 hour corpse run. <br>
On that day we had won. <br>
<br>
<br>
I made a new sig to celebrate feeling uber for a day<br>
